The configurator allows to associate specific item attributes to configured items. To manage attributes:

1.  Enable Attributes management from the Configurator Setup
2.  Enter Attribute Values in Characteristic and in Characteristic Values

<img width="" src="https://docs-test.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000340-0/PCS1_ENU.png"><br>

<img width="" src="https://docs-test.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000340-0/Attributes2_ENU.png"><br>

The configured items show the attribute values according to the value of the characteristics used. Functionality available only if you use the configurator to generate item codes.

<img width="" src="https://docs-test.eos-solutions.it/Images/PR000340-0/Attributes3_ENU.png"><br>

In the product configurator setup there is also a field, called **Copy attributes from neutral item**, which, if enabled, copies all attributes (those not associated with a characteristic) from the neutral item to the configured item.

<br>
